 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  result  of  sex  that  is  related  to  the  purpose  of  sex ,  which  is  to  have  a  child .  S exp lo iter  is  not  a  result  of  sex ,  and  chicken  is  not  related  to  the  purpose  of  sex .  Rep ro ductive  cycle  is  a  result  of  sex ,  but  it  is  not  what  someone  wants .  Pro creation  is  a  result  of  sex ,  but  it  is  not  what  someone  wants .  Human  experience  is  a  result  of  sex ,  but  it  is  not  what  someone  wants .  So  the  answer  is  pro creation  ( d ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  where  a  check  is  usually  kept ,  not  a  place  where  a  check  is  used .  A  cash  register  is  where  cash  is  kept ,  not  a  check .  A  desk  drawer  is  a  common  place  to  put  a  check ,  not  a  fish  tank .  A  bank  is  where  a  check  is  deposited ,  not  a  place  to  hide  it .  A  pay  envelope  is  a  place  to  put  a  check ,  but  not  a  place  to  hide  it .  So  the  answer  is  desk  drawer  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  where  a  statue  is  found  on  a  platform .  A  platform  is  a  place  where  people  stand ,  and  a  statue  is  usually  found  on  a  platform .  Below  is  a  place  where  a  statue  is  found ,  but  not  on  a  platform .  Arena  is  a  place  where  people  stand ,  but  not  a  platform .  Concert  hall  is  a  place  where  people  stand ,  but  not  a  platform .  Museum  is  a  place  where  people  can  see  a  statue ,  but  not  on  a  platform .  Building  is  a  place  where  a  statue  can  be  found ,  but  not  on  a  platform .  So  the  answer  is  ( d )  museum .

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  related  to  the  unions  and  the  reason  for  the  strike .  The  unions  need  to  make  demands  that  are  reasonable ,  which  is  the  reason  for  the  strike .  More  money  is  a  common  demand ,  but  not  the  reason  for  the  strike .  Not  going  to  work  is  the  opposite  of  what  the  unions  are  doing .  Return  to  work  is  the  opposite  of  the  strike .  The  union  is  the  organization  that  the  strike  is  related  to .  So  the  answer  is  reasonable  ( a ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  related  to  pain  relief .  Taking  anal ges ics  is  to  relieve  pain ,  and  the  most  relevant  option  is  to  avoid  pain .  Accept ance  is  not  a  direct  action  to  pain  relief .  Ack nowled ment  is  not  a  direct  action  to  pain  relief .  Passing  grade  is  not  a  direct  action  to  pain  relief .  Intellectual  challenge  is  not  a  direct  action  to  pain  relief .  So  the  answer  is  avoid  pain  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  where  you  can  buy  a  replacement  for  an  ax  handle .  Bathroom  is  not  a  place  to  buy  an  ax  handle .  Water  fountain  is  not  a  place  to  buy  an  ax  handle .  Grocery  store  is  not  a  place  to  buy  an  ax  handle .  F ridge  is  not  a  place  to  buy  an  ax  handle .  Hardware  store  is  a  place  to  buy  an  ax  handle .  So  the  answer  is  hardware  store  ( b ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  thing  that  is  common  and  difficult  for  parents  to  do  when  a  baby  is  young .  Arr iving  early  is  a  problem  for  parents ,  but  it  is  not  a  thing  that  a  baby  can 't  do .  Learning  to  walk  is  a  milestone  that  a  baby  can  do .  Knowing  whether  a  baby  is  a  boy  or  girl  is  not  a  problem  for  parents .  Bringing  joy  is  a  positive  experience  for  parents .  Talking  nonsense  is  a  normal  phase  for  babies ,  but  it  is  not  a  problem  for  parents .  One  thing  that  makes  raising  a  baby  difficult  is  crying  and  needing  to  be  fed  all  the  time .  So  the  answer  is  not  in  the  options .  The  correct  answer  is  not  in  the  options .

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  way  to  enter  a  brown stone ,  which  is  a  type  of  a  building .  Brooklyn  is  a  place ,  not  a  way  to  enter .  Ring  is  a  door bell ,  not  a  way  to  enter .  Sub division  is  a  type  of  a  land ,  not  a  way  to  enter .  Br icks  are  a  material  of  a  building ,  not  a  way  to  enter .  New  York  City  is  a  place ,  not  a  way  to  enter .  The  way  to  enter  a  brown stone  is  through  a  door ,  and  the  answer  is  the  correct  one .  So  the  answer  is  none  of  the  options .

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  related  to  the  action  of  running .  P icking  up  pace  to  a  run  means  that  he  is  going  faster .  He  is  not  learning  to  walk ,  which  is  the  opposite  of  running .  He  is  not  frightened ,  which  is  not  related  to  running .  He  is  not  trying  to  learn  something ,  so  get  away  from  is  not  the  reason .  The  reason  is  to  exercise ,  which  is  the  most  relevant  among  all .  So  the  answer  is  exercise  ( d ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  place  that  is  known  for  beer .  A  condo  is  a  residential  area ,  and  a  city  is  a  place  with  many  buildings .  Electrical  circuit  is  not  a  place .  Sub urb ia  is  a  part  of  a  city .  Milwaukee  is  a  city  known  for  beer ,  and  it  is  also  the  city  where  you  can  find  a  condo .  So  the  answer  is  mil waukee  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  people  usually  do  after  having  sex .  Having  sex  is  a  private  activity ,  and  people  usually  shower  after  it .  Bedroom  is  where  people  have  sex ,  but  shower  is  not  a  part  of  the  bedroom .  Pleasant  is  a  feeling ,  not  an  activity .  Obesity  is  not  related  to  shower .  Pain ful  is  a  feeling ,  not  an  activity .  Dirty  is  a  feeling ,  but  shower  is  not  the  only  way  to  get  dirty .  So  the  answer  is  dirty  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  when  you  are  not  well  rested  and  it 's  a  rainy  day ,  which  is  a  common  situation  when  you  want  to  sleep .  Sleeping  is  the  most  common  thing  to  do  when  you  are  not  well  rested .  Writing ,  making  bread ,  and  staying  in  bed  are  all  related  to  sleeping .  Enjoy  film  is  a  way  to  relax  and  sleep .  So  the  answer  is  sleep  ( a ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  store  that  sells  jeans .  A  clothing  store  is  a  place  where  you  can  buy  clothes ,  including  jeans .  Bedroom  is  a  place  where  you  can  find  clothes  but  not  jeans .  Thr ift  store  is  a  place  where  you  can  find  clothes  at  a  low  price ,  but  not  necessarily  jeans .  Apartment  is  a  place  where  you  can  find  clothes  but  not  jeans .  Gap  is  a  store  that  sells  jeans .  So  the  answer  is  gap  ( e ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  part  that  is  very  light  and  hollow ,  which  is  the  wing .  Animals  have  different  types ,  and  some  fly  because  of  their  lightweight  hollow  wings .  T ails  are  not  hollow ,  bones  are  not  hollow ,  eyes  are  not  hollow ,  heads  are  not  hollow ,  and  bodies  are  not  hollow .  So  the  answer  is  wings  ( not  given ).

 Q  The  answer  must  be  a  situation  that  is  common  in  winter  and  for  young  boys .  Ski  is  a  winter  sport ,  but  not  for  young  boys .  Play  hockey  is  a  winter  sport  and  for  young  boys .  Summer  is  not  a  winter  season .  Kn it  is  a  winter  activity ,  but  not  for  young  boys .  Being  warm  is  not  a  winter  activity .  So  the  answer  is  play  hockey  ( b ).

 Q 